Célia Mara (born July 27, 1961) is a Brazilian singer-songwriter and producer who has lived since the 1990s in Vienna, Austria and since 2003 also partly in Salvador, Bahia.
In 1979, she was the first girl (and Female composer) of the Vale de Jequintinhonha participating to a regional event, "Los procurados" festival, organized by Tadeu Martins.
In 1993, she moved to Austria, having a solo and duo-career, performing at important regional jazz festivals Jazzfestival–Burghausen and Jazzfest–Jena.
In 1997, she founded the Austria-based Latin-band potênciaX – with Herwig Gradischnig, Ingrid Oberkanins and others.
Célia Mara is managed and produced since 1996 by Silvia Jura Santangelo.
On March 8, 2011, Célia Mara got the Austrian Citizenship by honor.

Célia Mara was born in Pedra Azul, Minas Gerais, a small town in the Vale do Jequitinhonha, one of today's poorest regions of the world.
In the early 1990s, her first European tour brought her to small clubs and minor festivals in Germany, Switzerland, Austria and Northern Italy.
